    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/45000120/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """PART 1: Fundamentals of plasticity
1. Introduction
Development of the course
Objectives
Program
Bibliography

2. The tensile test
Engineering stress-strain
True stress-strain
Maximum load
Stress-strain empirical laws
The simple compression test
The Bauschinger effect

3. Yield Criteria.
Isotropic materials definition.
Yield of metallic materials
Geometrical representation
Tresca and Von Mises Criteria?s
Non-metallic materials criteria
Coulomb Criterion
Drucker-Prager Criterion
Strain hardening effect

4. Constitutive equations
Introduction
Stress-strain relationship for isotropic materials
Stress-strain relationship for metallic materials
Hill equations
Prandtl-Reuss and Levy-Mises equations
Hencky equations

5. Viscoplasticity
Definitions
Creep and relaxation
Logarithmic creep and Andrade
Stress and temperature effects

6. Physics of plasticity.
Introduction to crystallography and microplasticity mechanisms
Thermally activated and drag controlled dislocation motion
Creep mechanisms based on diffusion and dislocation glide
Mechanical twinning and phase transformations

PART 2: Applications in PLASTICITY

7. Pure bending.
Hypotheses
Elastic moment and plastic moment
Plastic mechanisms

8. Plastification of beams
Analysis of the process
Isostatic and hyperstatic beams
Collapse loads
The extremum principle

9. Plastification of tubes
Analysis of the process
Thin wall tubes. Plastification of pipes and spheres.
Instability. Maximum pressure
Thick wall tubes.

PART 3: Solving problems using numerical simulations

S1. Exercise 1. The tensile test. Obtaining the stress-strain curve through a virtual test
Measurements of the strain using a longitudinal extensometer
Measurements of the strain using a transversal extensometer
Measurements of the stress from load
Bridgmann?s correction

S2. Exercise 2. The compression test.
Friction and barreling
Comparison Von Mises vs Drucker Prager
Study of the effects of the hydrostatic pressure on VM and DP

S3A. Exercise 3. Plastification of beams
The neutral axis under elastic and plastic behaviour
Measuring the maximum elastic bending moment
Measuring the maximum plastic bending moment

S3B. Exercise 3. Plastification of thick wall tubes
Tresca / Von Mises comparison
Plain strain / Plane stress comparison"""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/f.galvez%40upm.es> ;
